(43, 85, 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 3, 0, 6, 1141962977, 9, 3, 2006, 1141902511, 9, 3, 2006, 'published', 0, 'During the second year of Pierre Samuel''s marriage  to Made Le De, Victor Made', '<p align="right"><font face="tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>THE NEXT GENERATION</strong></font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">During the second year of Pierre Samuel&#39;s marriage to Made Le De, Victor Made was born with the</font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">Marquis de Mirabeau as his godfather. Victor Marie Du Pont (1767-1827) was<font color="#ffff33"> </font><font size="4" color="#669966">an aide-de-camp to</font></font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">Illuminatus Lafayette from 1789-1792. Whether Victor was a Mason in France before the family came</font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">to the United States in 1800, I do not know. Victor Marie DuPont soon got involved in Freemasonry in</font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">the United States after arriving. The following are some of the highlights to his secret Masonic career</font></p><p><font face="verdana,geneva">according to Masonic records.</font></p><p align="center"><font face="verdana,geneva" style="background-color: #0033cc" color="#ffffff">1808-signed a masonic petition to create a lodge at Angelica, NY</font></p><p align="center"><font face="verdana,geneva" style="background-color: #0033cc" color="#ffffff">1813--joined Washington Lodge No. 1 of Delaware</font></p><p align="center"><font face="verdana,geneva" style="background-color: #0033cc" color="#ffffff">1814-joined Knights Templars of Wilmington, Del.</font></p><p align="center"><font face="verdana,geneva" style="background-color: #0033cc" color="#ffffff">1819-Grand Marshall of the Grand Lodge of Delaware (also 1822, 1823, 1825, 1827)</font></p><p align="center"><font face="verdana,geneva" style="background-color: #0033cc" color="#ffffff">1825--Grand Treasurer of the Grand Lodge of Delaware</font></p><p align="center"><font f